Video of Prince Moulay Hassan of Morocco denying officials who want to kiss his hand has gone viral. (Al Aoula)

If you're looking for a new way to perfect your agile and cat-like reflexes, may we suggest attempting to kiss the Moroccan prince's hand?

This practice of kissing the hands of royals has lingered in Morocco, even under King Mohammed VI — much to the dismay of critics who decry it as an antiquated show of subservience. It persisted even after the Arab Spring
